Children's cold and cough medicines are under scrutiny by federal regulators due to insufficient testing in children.
Overdoses are common as many kids are given multiple medications.
Some products, like Concentrated Tylenol Plus Cold & Cough, have misleading labels.
Baltimore officials recommend avoiding over-the-counter cough and cold meds for kids under 5.
The FDA issued warnings about the risks, leading to recalls of certain infant products.
Safety experts suggest banning these medicines for children under 6.
Parents are urged to be cautious and consult healthcare providers before giving any medications to young children.
